  "logTail": [
    {
      "channel": "narration",
      "text": "The sentence stops. He stands a moment holding the rest of it, as if he has read it back and found it not worth the ink.",
      "count": 1
    },
    {
      "channel": "narration",
      "text": "\"Two hands left. You were standing here. That is all this is.\"",
      "count": 1,
      "speaker": "Naoyuki"
    },
    {
      "channel": "narration",
      "text": "He goes on along the veranda. He looked at you once.",
      "count": 1
    },
    {
      "channel": "narration",
      "text": "Genemon takes up the brush again. He asks the last of it plainly, at the volume he keeps for the board — the room hears him and does not listen.",
      "count": 1
    },
    {
      "channel": "narration",
      "text": "\"One thing before the ink. If a claim follows you here — a debt, a master, a magistrate — I have to write it in the book against you. So I ask you once. Is anything owing on you?\"",
      "count": 1,
      "speaker": "Genemon"
    },
    {
      "channel": "narration",
      "text": "\"Why keep me?\"",
      "count": 1,
      "speaker": "Nameless"
    },
    {
      "channel": "narration",
      "text": "\"You are the sixth. Understand what that means. I did not choose you — you were standing where a hand was missing. If a better sixth comes up that road, I will write him in and strike you out, and I will not be sorry. I would tell you the same day I wrote it. That is not a threat. It is what the book is for.\"",
      "count": 1,
      "speaker": "Genemon"
    },
    {
      "channel": "narration",
      "text": "\"The two that left?\"",
      "count": 1,
      "speaker": "Nameless"
    },
    {
      "channel": "narration",
      "text": "\"They left owing nothing, and nothing was owed to them. I struck their lines clean. The lowlands pay in coin, and they pay in winter, when a man has none. I could not argue against that, so I did not try.\"",
      "count": 1,
      "speaker": "Genemon"
    },
    {
      "channel": "narration",
      "text": "\"And if there were?\"",
      "count": 1,
      "speaker": "Nameless"
    },
    {
      "channel": "narration",
      "text": "\"Then the house is paid first, for as long as you eat its rice. Whoever else holds the claim can come and find you after that. So far nobody has come.\"",
      "count": 1,
      "speaker": "Genemon"
    },
    {
      "channel": "milestone",
      "text": "Rank ↑ — The day-hand 日雇",
      "count": 1
    },
    {
      "channel": "narration",
      "text": "You begin to mark the turning of the days, and the four seasons with them.",
      "count": 1
    },
    {
      "channel": "system",
      "text": "You find a stretch of wall out of the wind, set your back to it, and let your arms hang. The work will keep. So will you.",
      "count": 2
    },
    {
      "channel": "reward",
      "text": "Haul stores at the forecourt. (+20 coin)",
      "count": 1
    },
    {
      "channel": "narration",
      "text": "Coin, at last, and few enough to count on one hand. What little the house pays in mon, you keep your own tally of.",
      "count": 1
    },
